                            <comment id="12992616" author="laukik" created="Wed, 9 Feb 2011 17:42:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Support for concatenated gzip files is dependent on hadoop core, and is available since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6835&quot; title=&quot;Support concatenated gzip files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6835&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6835&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is fixed. For loading bz2, Pig implements a separate InputFormat, and this was silently ignoring the concatenated data when the input to be loaded is a concatenated bz2 file. Uploading a patch that makes the bz2 stream reader to raise an exception if it encounters additional data past the crc block.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
